claim.claim-text:
20. A method comprising: 
receiving first data corresponding to standard printed content of at least one issue of a periodical, the standard printed content including a plurality of articles; 
receiving second data indicating at least one category of content that is of interest to a subscriber to the periodical; 
generating customized index data based on the first data and the second data, in which the customized index data identifies at least one article of the plurality of articles; and 
outputting a customized index for the subscriber, the customized index including the customized index data, the customized index to be attached to one issue of the periodical, and in which the customized index is separate from the standard printed content of the at least one issue.

21. A method comprising: 
receiving first data corresponding to standard printed content of a periodical; 
receiving second data indicating at least one content preference of a subscriber to the periodical; 
generating customized index data based on the first data and the second data, in which the customized index data identifies first content included in the standard printed content; 
determining at least one hyper-footnote based on the customized index data, in which the at least one hyper-footnote corresponds to second content associated with the first content, and in which the second content is not included in the standard printed content of the periodical; and 
printing a customized index for the subscriber, the customized index including the customized index data and an indication of the at least one hyper-footnote, in which the customized index is separate from the standard printed content.
